## Performance

### Keep `"use client"` boundaries small

The `"use client"` directive marks everything in that file — and all its imports — as client JavaScript. A single large `"use client"` file pulls all its static and presentational parts into the client bundle.

- Client components over ~300 lines are a signal to split: extract static/presentational sections as Server Components, keep the interactive parts as small client leaves.
- A layout component that only needs a `useState` for one toggle should not be `"use client"` — extract the toggle as its own small client component.

```tsx
// wrong - entire page is client-side because of one dropdown
"use client"
export function ProductPage({ product }) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false)
  return (
    <div>
      <HeroSection product={product} />   {/* static, could be server */}
      <PriceTable prices={product.prices} /> {/* static */}
      <Dropdown open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen} /> {/* needs client */}
    </div>
  )
}

// correct - only the dropdown is client
export function ProductPage({ product }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <HeroSection product={product} />
      <PriceTable prices={product.prices} />
      <DropdownClient />   {/* "use client" isolated here */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Use `next/dynamic` for heavy below-the-fold components

Chart libraries, rich text editors, map components, and other heavy dependencies should be loaded lazily when they are not needed on initial paint.

```tsx
import dynamic from "next/dynamic"

const ProductChart = dynamic(
  () => import("@/components/products/ProductChart"),
  { loading: () => <ChartSkeleton />, ssr: false }
)
```

Use `ssr: false` only when the component uses browser-only APIs that would break SSR.

### No barrel `index.ts` re-exports

Barrel files cause bundlers to include the entire module in every chunk that imports any single export, breaking tree-shaking.

```ts
// wrong - any import from this barrel pulls in everything
// src/components/icons/index.ts
export { SearchIcon } from "./SearchIcon"
export { HeartIcon } from "./HeartIcon"
// ... 40 more

// correct - import directly from the source
import { SearchIcon } from "@/components/icons/SearchIcon"
```

Do not create new `index.ts` barrel files. If you need to add an export, add it directly to the source file and import from there.

### No heavy imports in skeletons or server components

Skeletons and Server Components must not import client-only libraries (chart libs, animation libraries, complex form libraries). This forces those libraries into the server bundle or the skeleton's chunk.

```tsx
// wrong - skeleton pulls in the entire recharts library
import { ProductChart } from "@/components/products/ProductChart" // "use client" + recharts

// correct - skeleton is standalone
import { ChartSkeleton } from "@/components/products/skeletons/ChartSkeleton"
```
